main event: A strange object was observed in the sky, causing power failures and flickering lights in the northeastern United States and southeastern Canada on November 9, 1965.
interesting points: Witnesses reported seeing a bright, fireball-like object in the sky around the time of the power failures.
The object seemed to be related to the flow of power from the Niagara-Mohawk power station, with oscillographs showing the Niagara system being drawn to capacity before the blackout.
There were also reports of other UFO sightings in the area around the same time, including a bell-shaped object hovering over Manhattan.
Some researchers suggested the electromagnetic effects of the UFOs may have contributed to the power failures, though the exact cause remained unclear.
The government and military were reportedly investigating the incidents, but details were not being publicly released.
sighted object: A bright, fireball-like object in the sky
location: Northeastern United States and southeastern Canada
witnesses: Multiple witnesses, including residents and officials
photographs: Yes, a photograph from Time Magazine showing a UFO over a munition factory that had a power failure
